### IDE / tooling
.idea/
.vscode-test
_tmp/
.worktrees/
.local/
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.claude/agent-memory/

### spec-spine derived artifacts
# The compiler owns .derived/; only the committed shards are tracked.
.derived/spec-registry/*
!.derived/spec-registry/by-spec/
.derived/codebase-index/*
!.derived/codebase-index/by-spec/
!.derived/codebase-index/by-package/
!.derived/codebase-index/config-hash.json
!.derived/codebase-index/slices.json

### napi platform-package payloads
# Built by the publish workflow and injected into the
# @statecrafting/toolchain-<platform> packages at pack time. Only the
# manifests + READMEs are tracked; the binaries never enter git.
packages/toolchain-*/encore-runtime.node
packages/toolchain-*/tsparser-encore

### vendored Encore build workspace
# The vendored encore.dev JS runtime is a published artifact: its built dist/
# IS the runtime and must be tracked, so it is exempted from the global
# node/dist rules above.
!vendor/encore/runtimes/js/encore.dev/dist/
